# Normalize line endings to LF on checkout across every platform. atago has
# golden/drift tests that regenerate files (the behavior docs under doc/e2e/, the
# schema examples under schema/examples/, and the docs-site samples under site/)
# with LF and compare them byte-for-byte against the committed copies. On Windows
# CI, git's autocrlf would otherwise check those files out with CRLF, so the
# regenerated LF output would never match. Forcing eol=lf keeps the comparison
# deterministic on Linux, macOS, and Windows alike.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be EOL-translated (would corrupt them and break the
# image-diff drift test and the image assertions).
*.png -text
*.gif -text
*.jpg -text
*.jpeg -text
*.ico -text
*.bin -text
*.pdf -text
